# [REGEXT](../wg/regext.html)

## Summary

The REGEXT Working Group met at IETF 126. The session was presided over by co-chairs Jim Galvin, Jorge Cano, and Antoine Verschuren. 

The working group highlighted its administrative transition from the Applications and Real-Time (ART) area to the Operations and Management (OPS) area, welcoming Mohamed Boucadair as the new Area Director (AD). A revised, streamlined charter was established to align with the OPS area framing while maintaining the same core responsibilities.

Key discussions focused on resolving the coordination issues among three foundational RDAP drafts (the "RDAP Triad") following an ad-hoc meeting of authors and chairs. The working group also introduced a pilot experiment to use GitHub for draft collaboration, starting with `draft-ietf-regext-epp-same-entity`. Several active and proposed documents were presented and discussed, covering domain name variants, DNSSEC delegation automation, and structured reliability assessment metadata.

